etymologies: mid 19th century; earliest use found in William S. Hamilton (1788–1856), philosopher. From classical Latin latēscent-, latēscēns, present participle of latēscere, inchoative of latēre to be hidden

definitions: That is or is becoming latent, hidden, or obscure.

notes.text: In later use with reference to the social behaviour of the Menominee Native Americans.
